The paper deals with visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision. The use of deep learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks, is mentioned, which suggests that the paper belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of motion cues, which are typically used in video analysis and classification tasks, indicating that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques for feature extraction and tracking also suggests that the paper may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on tracking-by-detection and robotics applications suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
